{"sequence":33,"timestamp":"2026-04-29T10:58:10.515209657Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-1-84e8db66","body":"Staleness validation is still bypassed by plan-derived lineage/task views. `src/contexts/milestone_record/service.rs:4135` reads the current plan via `load_plan_bundle_for_lineage()` without checking `snapshot.source_requirements_bundle`, and the same unvalidated path feeds `bead_execution_history()` at `src/contexts/milestone_record/service.rs:4198` and `list_tasks_for_milestone()` at `src/contexts/milestone_record/service.rs:4338`. CLI/read-model surfaces such as `milestone tasks` (`src/cli/milestone.rs:854`), `project show` (`src/contexts/project_run_record/service.rs:1501`), and run status labels (`src/cli/run.rs:3013`) can therefore continue rendering old bead titles/acceptance criteria after the source requirements bundle has been re-answered. This violates the bead requirement that plan renderers surface a structured stale result instead of silently using stale artifacts. Wire `RequirementsStorePort` plus the milestone snapshot into these lineage/task loaders, or return an explicit stale status, and add a regression covering a stale materialized source through at least one of these read-model paths.","classification":"fix_current_bead","dedup_key":"a16119993b5d27790ee8b639aa155f7e75035f7776e300be2443ae07ae65143a","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.5-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260429063855","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
