{"sequence":53,"timestamp":"2026-04-29T12:01:10.004033556Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-2-7c74f7e9","body":"src/cli/run.rs:916 and src/contexts/automation_runtime/success_reconciliation.rs:366 call the bead-selection flow directly after milestone task completion. That flow reaches src/contexts/milestone_record/service.rs:5262 and reads plan.json via load_runtime_bead_membership_refs without validating source_requirements_bundle freshness. A requirements re-answer can therefore leave CLI/daemon reconciliation selecting and claiming the next bead from the stale materialized plan, bypassing the new guards added to milestone next/run entrypoints. Move the freshness check into the shared runtime plan-membership load path or require snapshot/requirements stores in select_next_milestone_bead/select_next_milestone_bead_from_recommendation, and add a stale-source regression for post-completion selection.","classification":"fix_current_bead","dedup_key":"7ea99dc355aa5b4b62de079287a477cf6192034d1e6c05122138f4cbf4a5648c","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.5-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260429063855","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":54,"timestamp":"2026-04-29T12:01:10.031533568Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-2-215dc32e","body":"src/contexts/requirements_drafting/service.rs:2407-2430 falls back to the embedded bundle when the payload bundle is invalid, but still returns milestone_bundle_id from run.latest_milestone_bundle_id. The materializers then persist that id as the source at src/cli/project.rs:327-337 and src/cli/milestone.rs:383-393 even though the bundle used did not come from that payload. On the next downstream load, src/contexts/milestone_record/service.rs:3809-3823 tries to parse the invalid payload and reports a corrupt source, so a legacy handoff that extract_milestone_bundle_handoff explicitly accepts becomes immediately unusable after materialization. Track whether the authoritative payload was actually used, clear or repair the source id when falling back to embedded state, and add a regression that materializing an embedded-fallback handoff remains fresh.","classification":"fix_current_bead","dedup_key":"a5fb9313bc2ef0a8d15408921f1623c80602e7091d0d6c7f22001b70b6257925","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.5-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260429063855","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
